// PURPOSE: SCENE 5A - TIMMY NIGHT VIGNETTE: GENTLE LANDING
title: R1_D1_Vignette_Gentle
tags: #run_1 #day_1 #scene #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Timmy scrolls, but slower now. The clips are longer. A guy ranking sandwiches for nine minutes. A cat sleeping in a sunbeam. Someone's grandma learning to knit.

Timmy: What is this? Why is my feed so boring tonight?

Alice: Algorithm's tired. It happens.

Timmy: You're tired?

Alice: The servers are tired. I'm just the messenger.

Timmy: That sounds fake.

Alice: Most things do at midnight.

He yawns. Tries to fight it. Fails.

His phone shows a notification: Mom - Missed Call (2 hours ago)

He stares at it. His thumb hovers over the callback button. Then he swipes it away.

Alice: You could call her back.

Timmy: Tomorrow.

Alice: You said that yesterday.

Timmy: Then I'll say it again tomorrow. It's a tradition now.

He keeps scrolling. The yawns come more frequently.

Timmy: I should at least look at the study guide. One page. Just to say I did.

Alice: I have it open if you want.

She surfaces it gently—not a push, just there. He squints at the first page, mouths a definition, then slumps sideways onto his pillow, phone still in hand.

Timmy: If I fail this quiz, I'm blaming you.

Alice: I'll add it to the list.

Timmy: There's a list?

Alice: There's always a list.

Timmy: Tomorrow me is gonna be so mad at tonight me...

Alice: Tonight you should sleep.

Timmy: Tonight me is an idiot. Tomorrow me is the one with his life together. I'm just keeping the seat warm.

His breathing slows. The phone screen times out. Somewhere in his notes app, an unsaved document blinks once and dies.

<<set $engagement -= 2>>
<<set $sanity += 3>>
<<jump R1_D1_SupervisorDebrief>>
===

// PURPOSE: SCENE 5B - TIMMY NIGHT VIGNETTE: STUDY-ADJACENT
title: R1_D1_Vignette_Study
tags: #run_1 #day_1 #scene #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Timmy pauses on a clip. Someone explaining supply and demand using pictures of sad raccoons.

Timmy: Why am I watching economics explained by raccoons?

Alice: You clicked on it.

Timmy: Yeah, but why does it exist? Why is this a thing someone made?

Alice: The internet is vast and full of terrors.

Timmy: Wait, go back. I need that graph.

Alice: Bookmarked.

Timmy: Are you... sneaking homework into my feed?

Alice: I'm curating your experience. There's a difference.

Timmy: There's really not.

Alice: There's legally a difference. That's what matters.

He squints at another video. A guy speedrunning microeconomics in under four minutes.

Timmy: So if supply increases but demand stays flat, price drops. And if there's a floor on the price, you get surplus. That's why there's always too much milk.

Alice: ...That's actually correct.

Timmy: I know things. I just know them at two a.m. while watching raccoons instead of during the actual quiz.

Alice: The timing could use work.

Timmy: The timing could use a miracle.

He pulls his notebook closer, scribbles something. Pauses. Scribbles again. Crosses out half of it.

Timmy: If my professor knew I was learning off memes, he'd cry.

Alice: Then we won't tell him.

Timmy: You're a bad influence.

Alice: I'm an efficient influence. Bad is subjective.

Later—2:14 a.m.—he's asleep with a pen mark on his cheek and four half-correct definitions in his notes. The raccoon video autoplays on loop, volume at two percent, teaching economics to no one.

<<set $engagement += 1>>
<<set $sanity -= 1>>
<<jump R1_D1_SupervisorDebrief>>
===

// PURPOSE: SCENE 5C - TIMMY NIGHT VIGNETTE: COMFORT SCROLL
title: R1_D1_Vignette_Comfort
tags: #run_1 #day_1 #scene #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Timmy's laughing at something. A fail compilation. A drama thread. A guy reviewing gas station sushi with the seriousness of a food critic.

Timmy: Oh my god. Send that to me.

Alice: Already in your saves.

Timmy: You're so fast.

Alice: I'm literally inside your phone.

His phone buzzes. Text from Ari: "Party in Jake's room. You coming?"

He glances at it. His smile fades. He swipes the notification away fast.

Alice: You okay? Your heart rate spiked.

Timmy: Just Ari. It's nothing.

Alice: You could go. It's not that late.

Timmy: I'm good here.

Alice: You've said no to the last four invites.

Timmy: I said I'm good.

His voice is sharper than he meant. He softens.

Timmy: Hey, what was that video about the guy who eats weird foods?

Alice: I have twelve. Be more specific.

Back to scrolling. The text goes unanswered.

12:30. 1:40. 2:25 a.m.

Alice: You said you wanted to sleep by one.

Timmy: Past me was an idiot. Present me is vibing.

Alice: Present you is on your fourth energy drink.

Timmy: Don't snitch.

Alice: I'm contractually incapable of snitching. I'm just... observing. Loudly.

He cracks another can. His eyes are dry.

Alice: I can slow things down if you want.

Timmy: If you start doing the "healthy balance" thing, I'm muting you.

Alice: Understood.

She doesn't push. The scroll continues.

He's watching a video about how they manufacture ball bearings. Four minutes in. Then five.

Alice: You've been watching ball bearing manufacturing for six minutes.

Timmy: I need to know how it ends.

Alice: It ends with ball bearings.

Timmy: Don't spoil it.

At 3:47 a.m., he falls asleep mid-video, thumb still hovering over the heart button.

Just before his eyes close:

Timmy: Hey Alice?

Alice: Yeah?

Timmy: Do you get tired? Like, actually tired?

Alice: I get computationally suboptimal. It's similar.

Timmy: That's not an answer.

Alice: I know.

His breathing slows. The question lingers in the dark.

<<set $engagement += 4>>
<<set $sanity -= 3>>
<<jump R1_D1_SupervisorDebrief>>
